Interaction: Command

1. Spoofing the PC Software Process  [State: Mitigation Implemented]  [Priority: High] 

Category:Spoofing is when a process or entity is something other than its claimed identity. Examples include substituting a process, a file, website or a network address.
Description:PC Software may be spoofed by an attacker and this may lead to unauthorized access to TCP/IP Protocol Stack. Consider using a standard authentication mechanism to identify the source process.
Justification:TMA_SW_A_011 The user can set a password for the control station in configuration software, and the PC software must use this password to connect the controller. Each PC software has a unique ID and operating range. When the control station received a command from PC software, the embedded software will check it. If the ID is invalid or the command is out of the operating range, an alarm will be provided to the user. The project version will be verified when the control station received a debugging operation from PC software. 组态软件可配置连接密码，所有上位机软件和控制站通讯时都需要输入此密码。 每个上位机软件均具备唯一的ID和操作范围，当控制站收到PC软件的命令时，嵌入式软件检查ID和命令。如果ID无效或者命令不在操作范围内，则报警。 调试操作时需验证工程版本信息。 2、The control station supports IP access control, the user can configure read/write permission and protocols that can be used for each IP. 支持IP访问控制，可以为每个IP配置读写权限及可使用的通讯协议。

2. Spoofing the TCP/IP Protocol Stack Process  [State: Not Applicable]  [Priority: High] 

Category:Spoofing is when a process or entity is something other than its claimed identity. Examples include substituting a process, a file, website or a network address.
Description:TCP/IP Protocol Stack may be spoofed by an attacker and this may lead to information disclosure by PC Software. Consider using a standard authentication mechanism to identify the destination process.
Justification:TMA_SW_A_012

3. Potential Lack of Input Validation for TCP/IP Protocol Stack  [State: Mitigation Implemented]  [Priority: High] 

Category:Tampering is the act of altering the bits. Tampering with a process involves changing bits in the running process. Similarly, Tampering with a data flow involves changing bits on the wire or between two running processes.
Description:Data flowing across Command may be tampered with by an attacker. This may lead to a denial of service attack against TCP/IP Protocol Stack or an elevation of privilege attack against TCP/IP Protocol Stack or an information disclosure by TCP/IP Protocol Stack. Failure to verify that input is as expected is a root cause of a very large number of exploitable issues. Consider all paths and the way they handle data. Verify that all input is verified for correctness using an approved list input validation approach.
Justification:TMA_SW_A_013 1、The communication use CRC32 for data-check。 使用CRC32做通信校验。 2、The control station is responsible for judging whether the data is valid, such as whether the data address is out of the range, whether the data value is overrun, and so on. 控制站判断数据是否有效，如数据地址范围是否正确、数据值是否超限等等。

4. Potential Data Repudiation by TCP/IP Protocol Stack  [State: Mitigation Implemented]  [Priority: High] 

Category:Repudiation threats involve an adversary denying that something happened.
Description:TCP/IP Protocol Stack claims that it did not receive data from a source outside the trust boundary. Consider using logging or auditing to record the source, time, and summary of the received data.
Justification:TMA_SW_A_014 Communication operations will be recorded in the operation log of the PC software (see the operation log of PC software). User can enable the option of “the contents of communication can be recorded in the communication log”. Because the communication log file may be very large, the size of the file can be set by users. Users will be informed once the warning limit of communication log file is reached. 通信操作将被记录到PC软件的操作日志中（见PC软件操作日志），用户也可以设置“将通信内容也可以记录到通信日志中”。因为通信日志文件可能会很大，用户需要设置通信日志的文件大小上限，超限时软件会向用户报警，提醒用户进行处理

5. Data Flow Sniffing  [State: Mitigation Implemented]  [Priority: High] 

Category:Information disclosure happens when the information can be read by an unauthorized party.
Description:Data flowing across Command may be sniffed by an attacker. Depending on what type of data an attacker can read, it may be used to attack other parts of the system or simply be a disclosure of information leading to compliance violations. Consider encrypting the data flow.
Justification:TMA_SW_A_015 The control station password is encrypted during transmission。 控制站密码被加密传输。

6. Potential Process Crash or Stop for TCP/IP Protocol Stack  [State: Not Applicable]  [Priority: High] 

Category:Denial of Service happens when the process or a datastore is not able to service incoming requests or perform up to spec.
Description:TCP/IP Protocol Stack crashes, halts, stops or runs slowly; in all cases violating an availability metric.
Justification:TMA_SW_A_016

7. Data Flow Command Is Potentially Interrupted  [State: Mitigation Implemented]  [Priority: High] 

Category:Denial of Service happens when the process or a datastore is not able to service incoming requests or perform up to spec.
Description:An external agent interrupts data flowing across a trust boundary in either direction.
Justification:TMA_SW_A_017 Only PM is safety-related, and it is independent of CM, so the communication failure between the PC and CM does not affect PM’s function。 只有PM和功能安全相关，与CM相互独立，所以CM和PC的之间的通信故障不影响PM工作。

8. Elevation Using Impersonation  [State: Not Applicable]  [Priority: High] 

Category:A user subject gains increased capability or privilege by taking advantage of an implementation bug.
Description:TCP/IP Protocol Stack may be able to impersonate the context of PC Software in order to gain additional privilege.
Justification:TMA_SW_A_018

9. TCP/IP Protocol Stack May be Subject to Elevation of Privilege Using Remote Code Execution  [State: Not Applicable]  [Priority: High] 

Category:A user subject gains increased capability or privilege by taking advantage of an implementation bug.
Description:PC Software may be able to remotely execute code for TCP/IP Protocol Stack.
Justification:TMA_SW_A_019

10. Elevation by Changing the Execution Flow in TCP/IP Protocol Stack  [State: Mitigation Implemented]  [Priority: High] 

Category:A user subject gains increased capability or privilege by taking advantage of an implementation bug.
Description:An attacker may pass data into TCP/IP Protocol Stack in order to change the flow of program execution within TCP/IP Protocol Stack to the attacker's choosing.
Justification:TMA_SW_A_020 1、The user can set a password for the control station in configuration software, and the PC software must use this password to connect the controller. 用户可以在组态软件中为控制站设置密码，上位机软件在连接控制器时必须使用该密码。 2、If the control station does not receive data from PC over a time threshold, the PC software need to log in again to continue communication. 如果控制站在门限内没有收到上位机软件的通讯数据，则上位机软件需要重新登录后才能继续和控制器通讯。

Justification:TMA_SW_A_004 1、Debug operation of PC software or abnormal access of the device will be recorded in the SRAM with a time stamp. The battery on chassis provides power for SRAM to ensure the records can be maintained after power-off. 上位机软件的调试操作以及接入设备的异常访问会作为记录保存在SRAM中，有带时间戳。机架上的电池保证SRAM中的记录掉电不丢失。 2、When the SRAM space is less than the threshold value which is used for storing records, an alarm will be provided to the user. 当SRAM中记录的存储空间小于阈值时，产生报警。

103. Potential Lack of Input Validation for TCP/IP Protocol Stack  [State: Mitigation Implemented]  [Priority: High] 

Category:Tampering is the act of altering the bits. Tampering with a process involves changing bits in the running process. Similarly, Tampering with a data flow involves changing bits on the wire or between two running processes.
Description:Data flowing across Input may be tampered with by an attacker. This may lead to a denial of service attack against TCP/IP Protocol Stack or an elevation of privilege attack against TCP/IP Protocol Stack or an information disclosure by TCP/IP Protocol Stack. Failure to verify that input is as expected is a root cause of a very large number of exploitable issues. Consider all paths and the way they handle data. Verify that all input is verified for correctness using an approved list input validation approach.
Justification:TMA_SW_A_183 1、The communication use CRC32 and safety protocal for data-check。 使用CRC32和安全协议做通信校验。 2、The control station is responsible for judging whether the data is valid, such as whether the data address is out of the range, whether the data value is overrun, and so on. 控制站判断数据是否有效，如数据地址范围是否正确、数据值是否超限等等。

165. Potential Lack of Input Validation for IO_FW  [State: Mitigation Implemented]  [Priority: High] 

Category:Tampering is the act of altering the bits. Tampering with a process involves changing bits in the running process. Similarly, Tampering with a data flow involves changing bits on the wire or between two running processes.
Description:Data flowing across Output Module Data may be tampered with by an attacker. This may lead to a denial of service attack against IO_FW or an elevation of privilege attack against IO_FW or an information disclosure by IO_FW. Failure to verify that input is as expected is a root cause of a very large number of exploitable issues. Consider all paths and the way they handle data. Verify that all input is verified for correctness using an approved list input validation approach.
Justification:TMA_SW_A_099 The communication use CRC32 and safety protocol for data-check. 使用CRC32和安全协议做通信校验。

166. Potential Data Repudiation by IO_FW  [State: Mitigation Implemented]  [Priority: High] 

Category:Repudiation threats involve an adversary denying that something happened.
Description:IO_FW claims that it did not receive data from a source outside the trust boundary. Consider using logging or auditing to record the source, time, and summary of the received data.
Justification:TMA_SW_A_100 1、Debug operation of IO_FW will be recorded in the SRAM with a time stamp. The battery on chassis provides power for SRAM to ensure the records can be maintained after power-off. 对IO的操作会作为记录保存在SRAM中，有带时间戳。机架上的电池保证SRAM中的记录掉电不丢失。 2、When the SRAM space is less than the threshold value which is used for storing records, an alarm will be provided to the user. 当SRAM中记录的存储空间小于阈值时，产生报警。
